hands_on_practices.solution:
1. The reduced vdW equation is  
$$\left(P_r+\frac{3}{V_r^2}\right)\,(3V_r-1)=8T_r.$$  
Solve for $P_r$:  

$$
P_r
=\frac{8T_r}{3V_r-1}-\frac{3}{V_r^2}.
$$

2. The compressibility factor is  

$$
Z=\frac{P\,V_m}{R\,T}
=Z_c\;\frac{P_r\,V_r}{T_r},\quad Z_c=\frac{3}{8}.
$$

3. For $T_r=\frac{6}{5}$ and $V_r=2$:

$$
P_r
=\frac{8\,(6/5)}{3\cdot2-1}-\frac{3}{2^2}
=\frac{48/5}{5}-\frac{3}{4}
=\frac{48}{25}-\frac{3}{4}
=\frac{192-75}{100}
=\frac{117}{100},
$$


$$
\frac{P_r\,V_r}{T_r}
=\frac{\frac{117}{100}\times2}{6/5}
=\frac{234/100}{6/5}
=\frac{234}{100}\cdot\frac{5}{6}
=\frac{39}{20},
$$


$$
Z
=\frac{3}{8}\cdot\frac{39}{20}
=\frac{117}{160}.
$$
